    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Marine cephalopods possessing a many-chambered external shell with simple septa; represented by a small number of extant species, but over 2,500 species flourished in the early Paleozoic era.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
